Presenting Problem / Chief Complaint: The patient wishes to discuss handling criticism related to their artistic work, expressing a desire to grow from feedback rather than feeling defeated.
History of Present Illness (HPI): The patient reflects on past experiences with criticism, noting initial personal hurt but has learned to separate their identity from their art.
Risk Assessment: The patient acknowledges feeling vulnerable about sharing personal stories through their photography but is working on embracing their unique experiences.
Current Functional Status: The patient reports feeling good about dedicating time to personal projects, experimenting with new techniques, and receiving positive feedback from peers.
Progress Evaluation: The patient feels they are making progress in their creative journey and building confidence in their work.
Therapeutic Interventions: The patient plans to continue challenging themselves with new projects and techniques, and to approach feedback with an objective mindset.
Next Steps: The patient intends to create a photography series that tells their story about transitioning to LA, while also exploring how to handle criticism constructively.
